f organising another migration, Friesen opted to help his community adapt to the changes taking place in the province. Included in the book are Friesen’s original sermons, translated for the first time from German, providing a rare glimpse into the Old Colony Mennonite theology that aided him in guiding the church in a strategy of gradual cultural accommodation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMennoniteszSaskatchewanvBiography. 0aOld Colony MennonitesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Cultural Heritage.2bisacsh1 aLoewen, Royden, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977573240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889775732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889775732/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles